tanzania_corridor_propagation_architecture
Corridor-Based Spatial Propagation Modeling Framework for Tanzania

Reproducible geospatial modeling architecture supporting the submission to the
International Journal of Applied Earth Observation and Geoinformation (JAG)

1. Scientific Contribution

This repository implements a reproducible geospatial modeling framework for corridor-constrained spatial propagation analysis in Tanzania using:

Earth Observation (EO) data

Socioeconomic indicators

Corridor-defined spatial adjacency

Spatial Durbin Modeling (SDM)

Unlike classical contiguity- or distance-based spatial models, this framework introduces a corridor-constrained spatial weights structure that restricts spatial spillovers to predefined infrastructure or development corridors.

This allows modeling of:

Directional development diffusion

Infrastructure-mediated propagation

Corridor-based spatial dependency

Policy transmission effects

The framework formalizes corridor propagation within an extended Spatial Durbin Model.

